article.description: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 77, Fairleigh Dickinson 67
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 77, Fairleigh Dickinson 67
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 77, Fairleigh Dickinson 67
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. -- Kelly Beidler tied a career-high with 22 points to lead Mount St. Mary's (Md.) to a 77-67 victory over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday night. Will Holland added 14 points and nine rebounds for the Mountaineers (11-14, 8-6 Northeast Conference), who have won six games in a row. A 3-pointer from Holland capped an 11-2 run for Mount St. Mary's in the second half that gave them a 56-44 lead with 11:48 remaining. A separate 6-0 run later in the half put the Mountaineers ahead 65-50 with 5:41 to play for their largest lead of the game. Mike Scott led the Knights (9-18, 8-6) with 14 points and nine assists. Alvin Mofunanya added 11 points and 12 rebounds. Mount St. Mary's shot 51 percent from the field (26-for-51), while Fairleigh Dickinson shot 41 percent (25-for-61).
